    • Method Detail

      • equals

        boolean equals(java.lang.Object o)
        Compares the specified object with this Node for equality. Note that this should not be implemented as a reference == comparison, but as a data comparison. Other things to keep in mind are that, because nodes are used as map keys, all the attributes used in the comparison between nodes must not change during the live of the object, so they should be declared final.
        Overrides:
        equals in class java.lang.Object
        Parameters:
        o - Object to compare with this
        Returns:
        true iff o is a Node, it's not null and is equal to this node

      • hashCode

        int hashCode()
        Returns a hash code value for this Node. It must return equal hash codes for equal nodes as defined in the equals(Object) method Note: Take a look at this link for guidelines on implementing this function
        Overrides:
        hashCode in class java.lang.Object
        Returns:
        a hash code value for the Node

      • isGreater

        boolean isGreater(Node n)
        Returns whether this Node is greater than the parameter node. This function is necessary for the Edge class to define edges to be truly undirected (no sense of source and destination)
        Parameters:
        n - The node to compare
        Returns:
        true iff this node is greater than n

      • toString

        java.lang.String toString()
        Returns a string representation of this Node. It should only print the key attributes of the node, not all its info.
        Overrides:
        toString in class java.lang.Object
        Returns:
        a string representation of this Node
